This paper deals with secure computation protocols and cryptographic tools, which are typically studied in the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also involves distributed computing, which falls under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The application of the protocol in evaluating trust relationships in a network suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of homomorphic encryption in the protocol indicates that it could be related to Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the use of ProVerif, a cryptographic protocol verification tool, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG), which often involves the use of verification tools.
